                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/20747</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Robertson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Monterey, Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 27, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that, upon information
                    which I consider reliable, Luis de la Rosa, the leader of several of the border
                    raids into the lower Rio Grande valley of Texas during the year 1915, will be
                    tried before a court-martial next week. The Department will be kept advised
                    regarding this.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Randolph Robertson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
